recitals:
WHEREAS, the Board of Directors has reviewed the strategic acquisition proposal for Silverlake Data Systems Ltd., a British Columbia corporation specializing in cloud infrastructure management;

WHEREAS, independent financial advisors from Hargrove Partners have delivered a fairness opinion dated February 12, 2026, concluding that the proposed acquisition price of CAD $47.5 million is fair from a financial standpoint to the shareholders of Crestview Holdings Inc.;

WHEREAS, legal counsel from Ashworth & Mackenzie LLP has completed due diligence and confirmed no material undisclosed liabilities or regulatory impediments to the transaction;

resolved_clauses:
NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED, that the Board of Directors hereby approves the acquisition of 100% of the outstanding shares of Silverlake Data Systems Ltd. for a total consideration of CAD $47,500,000, subject to customary closing conditions and regulatory approvals;

FURTHER RESOLVED, that the Chief Executive Officer and General Counsel are authorized to negotiate, execute, and deliver all definitive agreements, ancillary documents, and regulatory filings necessary to consummate the acquisition;

FURTHER RESOLVED, that a special committee comprising the Chair, CEO, and CFO is established to oversee integration planning and report to the Board on a monthly basis until integration is substantially complete.
